  Source:
    Title: Young India
    Editor: M. K. Gandhi
    Locus:
      Date: 27 Septemeber 1928
---
If observance of Truth was a bed of roses, if Truth cost one nothing and
was all happiness and ease, there would be no beauty about it. We must
adhere to Truth even if the heavens should fall.
